  "decision_conditions": [
    "The proposed ground floor rear extension and roof extension, by reason of their size, scale, and detailed design, would result in overly dominant, obtrusive, and incompatible forms of development that would fail to be subordinate to and respect the integrity of the subject property and the terrace of which it forms part. As such, the proposal is contrary to policies D3 (Optimising site capacity through the design-led approach), and D4 (Delivering good design) of The London Plan (2021) and policies LP1 (Design Quality and Local Character) and LP17 (Housing Design) of the Hackney Local Plan 2033 (2020), and the guidance contained within Hackney&#x27;s Residential Extensions and Alterations SPD (2009).",
    "The proposed ground floor side and rear extension by reason of its size and scale,&amp;nbsp; would result in a harmful impact on the amenities of the neighbouring occupiers at No. 20 and No.24 Mount Pleasant Lane by way of a loss of outlook, loss of daylight and sunlight, and would have an overbearing impact.&amp;nbsp; As such, the proposed development is contrary to policies D6 (Housing quality and standards) of the London Plan (2021), policy LP2 (Development and Amenity) of the Hackney Local Plan 2033 (2020), and the guidance contained within Hackney Residential Extensions and Alterations SPD (2009).&amp;nbsp;"
  ],
